cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CY

This paper discusses attacks on the Tor network, which is a system for anonymous communication. The attacks involve exploiting vulnerabilities in Internet routing, which suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of computer security (cs.CR), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and systems and control (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of monitoring frameworks to counter these attacks, which could place it in the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and cryptography and security (cs.CY).
